//=============================================================================
https://eslint.org/docs/user-guide/configuring
Configuring ESLint
Configuration Files - use a JavaScript, JSON or YAML file to specify configuration 
information for an entire directory (other than your home directory) and all of 
its subdirectories. This can be in the form of an .eslintrc.* file or an 
eslintConfig field in a package.json file, both of which ESLint will look for and 
read automatically, or you can specify a configuration file on the command line.
//=============================================================================